The paper proposes a biomolecular implementation of a theoretical model of computing device, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of DNA molecules as a medium for computation suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for optimizing the performance of the system, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a self-assembling system, which suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
